    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Process of plating with silver leaf on steel, iron, or occasionally brass, used especially on knives and scissors; patented in 1779 by Richard Ellis as a technique less expensive than French plating.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000021291/Newman, Illustrated Dictionary of Silverware (1987)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Proceso de chapado con láminas de plata sobre acero, hierro u ocasionalmente bronce, utilizado especialmente en cuchillos y tijeras. Patentado en 1779 por Richard Ellis como una técnica menos onerosa que el chapado francés.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Het met bladzilver plateren van staal, in het bijzonder van messen en scharen; in 1779 gepatenteerd door Richard Ellis als een techniek die goedkoper is dan de Franse plateermethode.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>將銀箔鍍於鋼、鐵，有時黃銅的過程，特別用於刀器與剪刀；於西元1779年，由李察•艾利斯(Richard Ellis)取得此項較法式鍍法便宜的技術專利。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
